claim.claim-text:
1. A process for influencing properties of combustion residue from a combustion process, in which fuel is burned on a grate of a combustion bed in a combustion chamber and accumulated unmelted or unsintered combustion residue derived from slag produced on the combustion bed is returned to the combustion process, the influencing process comprising:
regulating a melting process or sintering process in the combustion bed by returning the combustion residue to the combustion process only as long as, and only in such an amount that, a change in at least one essential combustion parameter caused by the return of the combustion residue remains within a predetermined tolerance limit;
wherein said step of regulating comprises monitoring the at least one essential combustion parameter and increasing or reducing the feed of combustion residue to the combustion process in response to said step of monitoring.
